This is an SVG Tutorial For beginner Developers!

The first step in the SVG Tutorial is to setup an HTML document using the correct HTML tags.
The tags are as follows:

<!Doctype html>
<html>
<head>
</head>
<body>
</body>
</html>

After the tags are properly setup, you may choose to start your SVG tag inside the body tag.

<!Doctype html>
<html>
  <head>
  </head>
    <body>
      <svg>
      </svg>
    </body>
</html>

The next step is to incorporate whichever SVG tags that are specific to your desire, an example of that may be to construct an SVG circle.

<!Doctype html>
<html>
  <head>
  </head>
    <body>
      <svg width="100" height="100">
           <circle cx="50" cy="50" r="40" stroke="green" stroke-width="4" fill="yellow" />
      </svg>
    </body>
</html>

One more example to use as a reference that is a little more in depth in terms of creativity is ellipses.

<!Doctype html>
<html>
  <head>
  </head>
    <body>
      <svg height="150" width="500">
        <ellipse cx="240" cy="100" rx="220" ry="30" style="fill:purple" />
        <ellipse cx="220" cy="70" rx="190" ry="20" style="fill:lime" />
        <ellipse cx="210" cy="45" rx="170" ry="15" style="fill:yellow" />
      </svg>
    </body>
</html>

With a better understanding of Scalable Vector Graphics through this Tutorial, developers have opened up a bridge for more creative endless opportunities.
Enjoy the Tutorial!
